article.description: Mount St. Mary's, Md. 93, St. Francis, Pa. 63
article.headline: Mount St. Mary's, Md. 93, St. Francis, Pa. 63
article.linkText: Mount St. Mary's, Md. 93, St. Francis, Pa. 63
article.story: EMMITSBURG, Md. -- Jeremy Goode scored 21 points to lead Mount St. Mary's to a 93-63 victory over St. Francis, Pa., on Saturday night. Jean Cajou finished with 19 for the Mountaineers (17-11, 12-5 Northeast Conference). Kelly Beidler added 18. Mount St. Mary's used a 10-2 run in the first half to jump out to a 37-21 lead with 8:59 left. At halftime, the Mountaineers led 49-34. In the second half, Mount St. Mary's went on a 16-3 run to hold the Red Flash (5-22, 2-14) scoreless for almost six minutes. Lamar Trice's layup with 6:50 remaining made the score 82-51. The Red Flash were led by Devin Sweetney, who finished with 21 points and 14 rebounds. Marquis Ford added 15 points. The Mountaineers shot 63.2 percent from the field (36-for-57) and totaled 20 assists.
